I have to admit that I had real trouble with today's mantra "I deserve".
Normally I can latch onto something when reciting Adrienne's daily mantra, but today I'm stumped.
"I deserve" sounds selfish or arrogant to me. Why should I deserve anything ? Do others not 'deserve' as well?
Please forgive me , I'm not trying to cause controversy , but for me this is a tough one and I'm wondering if anyone else feels this way?
I can get into " I hope for" or "I would Like" or even "I'm working towards". 
But "I deserve" sounds entitled and exclusive.
I know that 'Adrienne nation' is made up of all types but we all have one thing in common. We are trying to better ourselves.
So if someone out there can help me to feel OK with feeling like "I deserve" something I would appreciate it.
I can't get over the "I" part and I don't know why.
Like "I deserve to be loved" brings on thoughts of "Doesn't everyone deserve Love?".
I'm probably overthinking it but I can't think of anything that "I deserve".
I deserve to BE happy & live my life to the fullest! â¤

(for Adriene)

Yoga Charm
 (for Adriene)

Supine, long spine,
fingers entwined,
belly reclined,
seek the divine.

Soul shine.

Lift hips, chin dips, 
grasshopper sips,
Rest fingertips,
All thoughts eclipse,

Heart skips in bliss.

Take heart to earth,
let mind rebirth,
to know your worth.

Say it: I deserve.

Melt away, feet play.
Heart stay.

Namaste.
